{"key":"post-12328452","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12328452</id>\n<content>Perlite in a shotgun terrarium will not dry out.&amp;nbsp; This is because when you mist the cakes, the overspray replaces what has evaporated from the perlite in order to provide humidity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You don't cut back on FAE to maintain humidity.&amp;nbsp; If FAE causes a loss in humidity, you mist more.&amp;nbsp; Four to five air exchanges per hour are recommended.&amp;nbsp; A properly made and set up shotgun terrarium performs this level of air exchange automatically.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12328476</next>\n<prev>12328136</prev>\n<first>12327900</first>\n<last>12337403</last>\n<when>1270401616</when>\n<utime>04/04/10 08:20 PM</utime>\n</post>"}